# AI Maintenance (Background)

## Lifecycle

1. **Start** — at the beginning of every user prompt, launch `ai-maintenance-checker` in background (`is_background: true`)
2. **Parallel** — parent continues the primary task
3. **Default action** — `pnpm ai check` (read-only). Use `pnpm ai fix` only when repairing or on `init`.
4. **Await** — before final reply when the task touched AI surfaces (skills, rules, agents, hooks, `.claude/`, `AGENTS.md` mirrors, `scripts/ai.sh`)
5. **Skip await** — pure portal UI with zero AI-surface file changes

## Unified command (canonical)

```bash
pnpm ai          # status (default)
pnpm ai init     # cold start / first clone
pnpm ai onboard  # human + agent checklist
pnpm ai check    # validate only (CI)
pnpm ai fix      # safe repair + validate
```

Do **not** run scattered validate/sync scripts directly — they are merged into `pnpm ai`.

## Agent

- Entry: `.cursor/agents/ai-maintenance-checker.md`
- Script: `.cursor/agents/ai-maintenance-checker/scripts/run-maintenance.sh`
- Standard: `.cursor/standards/ai-system/STANDARD.md`

## Gold enforcement

Maintenance preserves:

- SOUL.md evidence contract
- `01-real-world-logic.mdc` OBSERVE→VERIFY loop
- `02-agent-scoring.mdc` Alignment Score
- No watered-down duplicate skills (merge or alias)
